text24.content: 1. Rabies: Rabies is a viral disease that spreads from the bite of an infected animal, such as a rabid dog. The disease is fatal without vaccination.The disease causes brain inflammation, fever, and delirium. Rabies vaccines are typically given after a bite, but some vaccines are used aspreventive treatment. It is classified as a neglected tropical disease.
